race.comment: CHARLESFORT (3) doesn't boast a great winning record but rarely turns in a poor performance and looks perfectly placed on this occasion. Battled on gamely into third behind TOKYO ICE here last time; now meets him 2kgs better and can turn the tables. TOKYO ICE (8) was a big improver here last time when sent forward and digging deep to hold them all at bay. Carries more weight this time but has to be taken seriously off that win. RAYMOND'S REWARD (2) is knocking on the door. Has good early pace, so will push to the front and give plenty of cheek. LIMBERING (10) proved less effective last time when ridden conservatively. Races best when pushed forward, though is expected to have company.
